Rating: 4
I made this recipe with just a few adjustments. When the pastry was cool, I heated a handful of semi-sweet chocolate chips in a plastic bag in the micro - snipped off the corner and drizzled chocolate over the top of all the pastries (top and bottoms) and then I sprinkled with chopped almonds. As for the fruit - I used fresh blueberries, blackberries and sliced strawberries. I didn't toss them in the jelly sauce, but drizzled the sauce over the top and around the plate. It was just enough. This dessert was fantastic. The chocolate and almonds were a perfect addition. Highly recommend.

